--------------------------------------------------
1. zajimavy screenshot https://www.starwindsoftware.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/RVTools-and-vCPU-TAB.png
2. _vms/<vm_guid>/statistics. jako psycho, ale bylo by gut - _vms/<vm_guid>/diskattachments - ulozit id disku, pak _disks/<id>/statistics a ty latency,
"hej, ktery vmko tak kurevsky zapisuje na storage?" - otazka, stejne jako "ktery vmko tak vytezuje sit?". thx. imo jsou 2 druhy pouziti -
admnistrace, tj. zjisteni, kde co je a praci s tim - smazat/presunout/..., a investigace - co jede pomalu, co neco zere,..,
ale jako ze chces "static" data a "dynamic" data, to byl smysl vety
--------------------------------------------------
ked pridavam nieco do toho co sa ma zobrazovat tak:
    1. pridam metodu do low
    2. pridam vypisanie do high
    3. v hight pridam flag (1 na viac)
    4. vo validate_filter poposuvam listy str a float

------------------------------------------------------------

imo toto:
- _vms
- _disks
- hosts
- storage domains
- clusters
- data centers
+ snapshots, obcas je se snapshoty problem, takze nejaky query na to jestli jsou s pameti,
  v preview atp...

object view:
- _vms + sloupce, prvne "staticke", pak "dynamicke" (statistics) + snapshot name|snapshot date|snaphost _status
  + console type urcite
    pokud ma napr. vice disku, vypsat v GUI vzdy prvni plus nejaky symbol znazornujici, ze existuje vice zaznamu
      priklad: foo_disk1[+]
      kliknuti na [+] by mohlo prepnout object view na typ sloupce, eg. _disks view, a aplikovalo by to filter
        napr. kde vmnane = foo
- _disks, vicemene ok
- hosts - nedaval bych vypis vsech vm v tomto view, spis 'pocet vm' 113[+] => odkaz na _vms view a filter kde hostname = $_host
- clusters - podobne jako hosts, rozhodne macrange a vypocitat allocation mac adres!
- data centers - podobne jako vyse
- templates = _vms vlastne, ale nebezi
- _nics + mac _address, driver (virtio/em/rltk)...


typicke sysadmin "pohledy":

- hosty s urcitou verzi vdsm/libvirtu/kernelu => ktere jsou ready na update?
  tedy takovy pre-upgrade investigation
- storage, nejaky storage se zaplnuje nebo je potreba decommision urciteho
  storage hw a tudiz zmigrovata data na jinou storage
  priklad: storage Foo je 1TB, kolik tam zabiraji disky vmek data? kolik budeme potrebovat
  mista na novou storage?


------- znacky ---------------
* = vypisat len 1. alebo vypisat kazde do noveho riadku?
info = ake dalsie info?, vypisat statistiky?
------- vv toto uz je --------
_vms - name, _status, id, _cluster version, _host, _memory, max memmory, _os, _template, statistiky vm (9), disk id (bootable), statisktiky disku (5), nic id (1.), stat. nic (8)
_disks - name, vm name (pre kazdu vm novy riadok), stat. vm (9), _status, id, actual size, provisioned size, _format, content type, storage type, stat. disk (5)
hosts - name, vm name (pre kazdu vm novy riadok), stat. vm (9), _status, id, _address, _cluster, nic (1.), stat. _host (17)
------- vv toto este nie -----
clusters - name, version, error handling, cpu, fencing policy, firewall type, data center (info), hosts (*, info), _vms (*, info), _networks (*, info), affinity groups/labels
data centers - name, _status, version, supported version, storage domains (*, info), _networks (*, info), clusters (*, info)
storage domains - name, _status, master, type, storage type, storage _address, _format, available space, used space, data center (info), _vms (*, info), _disks (*. info)
templates - name, _status, version, mem. guaranteed, mem. max, _cluster (info), data center (info), _vms (*, info), _nics (*, info), _disks (*, info), storage domain (info)
_nics - name, network (info), data center (info), version, _vms (*, info), tempaltes (*, info)
_networks - name, data center (info), _nics (*, info), clusters (*, info), hosts (*, info), _vms (*, info), templates (*, info)
pools - ?
volumnes - ?